Alex,

after a quick glance on your draft, it seems to me that you do not use
the 6lowpan adaptation layer, so it would be out of charter for 6lo
(but possibly in scope of 6man). The relevant part of our charter is:

1. IPv6-over-foo adaptation layer specifications using 6LoWPAN
technologies (RFC4944, RFC6282, RFC6775) for link layer technologies of
interest in constrained node networks


